Second Lady Karen Pence hosted a working lunch with leaders from the Department of Defense (DoD), Department of Veteran Affairs (VA), and the National Endowment for the Arts (NEA) Creative Forces Network. The purpose of the meeting was to highlight the effectiveness of creative arts therapies for military service members and veterans struggling with mental health issues such as PTSD. The meeting also aimed to encourage collaboration between government agencies to expand art therapy services for military populations. The meeting included presentations by various individuals and discussed the positive impact of art therapy on military service members and veterans.